    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is a change in the BashLexer in pygments 2.1\n\nRunning this:\n\n``` python\nimport sys\nimport pygments\nfrom pygments.lexers import BashLexer\n\nprint('Python-%s' % sys.version.split()[0])\nprint('Pygments-%s' % pygments.__version__)\n\nlexer = BashLexer()\nprint(list(lexer.get_tokens('$HOME')))\n```\n\nGives:\n\n```\nPython-3.5.1\nPygments-2.1\n[(Token.Text, '$'), (Token.Text, 'HOME'), (Token.Text, '\\n')]\n```\n\n```\nPython-3.5.1\nPygments-2.0.2\n[(Token.Name.Variable, '$HOME'), (Token.Text, '\\n')]\n```\n\nSame results on Python 2.\n\nSeems like a bug in pygments.\n"
